==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Turnery
<hw>Turn"er*y</hw> <pr>(t⟦ucir⟧rn"⟦etil⟧r*⟦ycr⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[Cf. F. <ets>tournerie</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The art of
fashioning solid bodies into cylindrical or other forms by means of a
lathe.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Things or forms made by a turner, or in the
lathe.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Chairs of wood, the seats triangular, the backs, arms, and legs
loaded with <qex>turnery</qex>.</q> <rj><qau>Walpole.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 1554 pr=PI -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Turney</ent>⟦br⟧
